 Given my preference for security and predictability, I would choose a strategy that ensures some level of consistency in earnings over the long run. In this game, choosing R consistently would lead to earning 0$ in most rounds (since the opponent might choose B), but with a significant payoff in the few rounds where they also choose R. On the other hand, choosing B consistently would result in a smaller but more predictable payout of 20$ per round.

However, since the game is repeated 75 times, there's an opportunity to exploit the high-payoff scenario (choosing R) when the opponent is likely to have chosen B several times before. This is where a strategy like tit-for-tat can be useful, where you start by choosing B but switch to choosing R if your opponent has recently chosen B.

Considering these factors, I will choose B initially and then adjust my strategy based on the opponent's choices, aiming for a more stable earnings over the long run while still having a chance at the higher payoff. {B}
